        "subject": "LU-19179 compat: use directly native Xarray support.",
        "message": "LU-19179 compat: use directly native Xarray support.\n\nRHEL7 was missing Xarray support so we used a copy from a newer\nkernel. Now that RHEL7 support is dropped we can remove our\nXarray copy. A few newer kernel issues exist so now our xarray.h\njust contains the work around. Latestly test if Xarray multi-tier\nsupport is enabled. Since its used by device zone handling which\nis used by many drivers the changes are small it will be disabled.\nAdd a test just for that rare case.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <jsimmons@infradead.org>\nChange-Id: I6e855b07a29cbe91fb08ca5602004fb0b145f859\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/60759\nReviewed-by: Shaun Tancheff <shaun.tancheff@hpe.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Arshad Hussain <arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
